<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[701,1228,339,1754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
DIAGNOSIS: Members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1041,1177,488,512]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1041,1177,488,512]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from all other leiognathids by a combination of large adult body size (. 
<quantity box="[732,825,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 mm</quantity>
SL), the absence of large round blotches of pigment on the flank, and the presence of a strongly ventrally protracting mouth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[701,1228,339,1754]" lastBlockId="4.[128,654,211,942]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
REMARKS: Members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1012,1148,696,720]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1012,1148,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further distinguished from all other ponyfishes, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1815" box="[872,950,755,779]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[872,950,755,779]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Equula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the presence of a nonsexually dimorphic light organ. The absence of flank pigmentation or the possession of faint yellowish or grayish-yellow vermiculate lines or vertical bars on the dorsal flank also distinguishes members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[1092,1228,903,927]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1228,903,927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other ponyfishes, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1815" box="[1142,1220,932,956]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1142,1220,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Equula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[878,1014,962,986]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[878,1014,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further distinguished from members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1815" box="[1068,1146,991,1015]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1146,991,1015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Equula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a strongly concave lower jaw profile (versus straight or nearly straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1815" box="[701,779,1080,1104]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[701,779,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Equula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). All explicit phylogenetic studies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T.N.Gill" authorityYear="1893" box="[701,864,1109,1133]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Leiognathidae</taxonomicName>
to date have recovered a paraphyletic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[867,1003,1139,1163]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,1003,1139,1163]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ikejima, K. &amp; N. B. Ishiguro &amp; M. Wada &amp; M. Nishida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="904 - 909" refId="ref5986" refString="Ikejima, K., N. B. Ishiguro, M. Wada, K. Kita- Tsukamoto, and M. Nishida. 2004. Molecular phylogeny and possible scenario of ponyfish (Perciformes: Leiognathidae) evolution. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 31: 904 - 909." type="journal article" year="2004">Ikejima et al., 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap" box="[777,1094,1168,1192]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6549" refString="Sparks, J. S., and P. V. Dunlap. 2004. A clade of non-sexually dimorphic ponyfishes (Teleostei: Perciformes: Leiognathidae): phylogeny, taxonomy, and description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3459: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2004">Sparks and Dunlap, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap &amp; W. L. Smith" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref6599" refString="Sparks, J. S., P. V. Dunlap, and W. L. Smith. 2005. Evolution and diversification of a sexually dimorphic luminescent system in ponyfishes (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), including diagnoses for two new genera. Cladistics 21: 305 - 327." type="journal article" year="2005">Sparks et al., 2005</bibRefCitation>
; Chakrabarty et al., MS). In accordance with the results of these studies, we restrict the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[926,1062,1257,1281]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[926,1062,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the clade containing the 
<typeStatus box="[873,921,1287,1311]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Forsskal, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="equulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus equulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Forsskal, P." box="[750,921,1316,1340]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refId="ref5734" refString="Forsskal, P. 1775. Descriptiones animalium avium, amphibiorum, piscium, insectorum, vermium; quae in itinere orientali observavit. Post mortem auctoris edidit Carsten Niebuhr: 1 - 20 + i - xxxiv + 1 - 164, Hauniae [Copenhagen]: Moller." type="book" year="1775">Forsskål, 1775</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6549" refString="Sparks, J. S., and P. V. Dunlap. 2004. A clade of non-sexually dimorphic ponyfishes (Teleostei: Perciformes: Leiognathidae): phylogeny, taxonomy, and description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3459: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2004">Sparks and Dunlap, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), and two other described species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sparks and Dunlap, 2004" authorityName="Sparks and Dunlap" authorityYear="2004" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[701,951,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus robustus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6549" refString="Sparks, J. S., and P. V. Dunlap. 2004. A clade of non-sexually dimorphic ponyfishes (Teleostei: Perciformes: Leiognathidae): phylogeny, taxonomy, and description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3459: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2004">Sparks and Dunlap, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="James and Badrudeen, 1990" authorityName=", James and Badrudeen" authorityYear="1990" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[842,1078,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus striatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="James, P. S. B. R. &amp; M. Badrudeen" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="217 - 226" refId="ref6082" refString="James, P. S. B. R., and M. Badrudeen. 1990. A new species of silverbelly Leiognathus striatus (Family Leiognathidae: Pisces) from the Gulf of Mannar, India and redescription of Leiognathus fasciatus (Lacepede). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of India 32: 217 - 226." type="journal article" year="1990">James and Badrudeen, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species rarely mentioned in the literature and even more rarely encountered in museum collections. This restricted concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[844,980,1523,1547]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[844,980,1523,1547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recovered as the sister group to all other members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T.N.Gill" authorityYear="1893" box="[701,867,1582,1606]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Leiognathidae</taxonomicName>
, less 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1815" box="[955,1033,1583,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[955,1033,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Equula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 1). Other ponyfish species in the literature currently referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[839,975,1641,1665]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[839,975,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not included in our restricted concept of this genus, are provided novel or resurrected generic assignments below on the basis of apomorphic morphological features. The lineage labeled ‘‘‘ 
<emphasis box="[149,174,241,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L.</emphasis>
’ sp. Sri Lanka’’ in figure 1 is recovered as a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[276,412,270,294]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,412,270,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Leiognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Chakrabarty et al. (MS). The taxonomy of this group is further dealt with in that manuscript rather than here, because the species-level status of ‘‘ 
<emphasis box="[533,558,358,382]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">L.</emphasis>
’’ sp. 
<collectingCountry name="Sri Lanka" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
cannot be determined due to a lack of morphological vouchers (only a tissue sample was available to 
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap &amp; W. L. Smith" box="[322,539,446,470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref6599" refString="Sparks, J. S., P. V. Dunlap, and W. L. Smith. 2005. Evolution and diversification of a sexually dimorphic luminescent system in ponyfishes (Teleostei: Leiognathidae), including diagnoses for two new genera. Cladistics 21: 305 - 327." type="journal article" year="2005">Sparks et al., 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[128,654,211,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", James and Badrudeen" authorityYear="1990" box="[154,388,477,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[154,388,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Leiognathus striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its congeners by the presence of an extremely deep body with a strongly convex dorsal profile (owing to the presence of a pronounced occipital hump) and a pigmentation pattern on the dorsal flank comprising broad yellow vertical bars. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sparks and Dunlap" authorityYear="2004" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Leiognathus robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its congeners by the absence of a pronounced occipital hump and the presence of a mildly sloping predorsal profile (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sparks, J. S. &amp; P. V. Dunlap" box="[295,642,771,795]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6549" refString="Sparks, J. S., and P. V. Dunlap. 2004. A clade of non-sexually dimorphic ponyfishes (Teleostei: Perciformes: Leiognathidae): phylogeny, taxonomy, and description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3459: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2004">Sparks and Dunlap, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[128,366,801,825]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Leiognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="equulus">
<emphasis box="[128,366,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Leiognathus equulus</emphasis>
